According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Companion Diagnostics Market was valued at USD 7.1 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 7.8 billion in 2026 to USD 14.3 billion by 2034, exhibiting a CAGR of 8.1% during the forecast period. The market is expanding rapidly as precision medicine becomes an integral component of modern healthcare, particularly in oncology. Growing adoption of targeted therapies, increasing prevalence of cancer and chronic diseases, rapid advances in genomic sequencing technologies, and expanding regulatory support for personalized medicine are collectively driving demand for companion diagnostic solutions worldwide.
